  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nThere are too many gossiped blocks sent to us with very old slot (out of the mcache windows and configured `seenTTL`)\r\n\r\n```\r\ngrep -e \"Received gossip block\" -rn beacon-2023-04-21.log | grep \"16Uiu2HAm3BTpUhsPgCPTYPJQ5EBH6DFTtVS7mMaKFioNYNChqrPi\" | grep \"curentSlot=6267911,\" | wc -l\r\n122\r\n\r\ngrep -e \"Received gossip block\" -rn beacon-2023-04-21.log | grep \"16Uiu2HAm3BTpUhsPgCPTYPJQ5EBH6DFTtVS7mMaKFioNYNChqrPi\" | grep \"curentSlot=6267919,\" | wc -l\r\n133\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe received more than 100 gossiped blocks per slot, ideally we should receive only 1!\r\n\r\nsome example logs\r\n```\r\n64910:Apr-21 01:02:41.674[network]       verbose: Received gossip block slot=6259233, root=0xb1fd…6653, curentSlot=6267911, peerId=16Uiu2HAm3BTpUhsPgCPTYPJQ5EBH6DFTtVS7mMaKFioNYNChqrPi, delaySec=104140.46600008011, recvToVal=2.2079999446868896\r\n64911:Apr-21 01:02:41.690[network]       verbose: Received gossip block slot=6264267, root=0x950c…c3a6, curentSlot=6267911, peerId=16Uiu2HAm3BTpUhsPgCPTYPJQ5EBH6DFTtVS7mMaKFioNYNChqrPi, delaySec=43732.46900010109, recvToVal=2.2209999561309814\r\n64912:Apr-21 01:02:41.708[network]       verbose: Received gossip block slot=6266950, root=0x1d9b…65c3, curentSlot=6267911, peerId=16Uiu2HAm3BTpUhsPgCPTYPJQ5EBH6DFTtVS7mMaKFioNYNChqrPi, delaySec=11536.471999883652, recvToVal=2.2360000610351562\r\n```\r\n\r\nright now we only ignore them after the deserialization which take our cpu time\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n- Quick check the message slot, ignore them it's it's too old before sending to our queue\r\n- Apply for all topics, not just `beacon_block`\r\n- Right now the peer sending us these messages are identified as \"Unknown\", we should print agent id instead\r\n- Inform client team if it happens frequently, it's likely a gossip issue, we only want to gossip messages in the first 3 windows of the mcache (3 * 0.7 = 2.1s)\r\n- Potentially penalize that peers? \r\n",
